Subject New Weight System~
Text
Ok.. this one has been a long overdue issue, and has finally been
addressed. Up to this point, armor and weapons had all kinds of random
wacky weights IF they had any at all...  So:
 
After consulting ye olde weight guides in me 3rd Ed. D&D book, and
making some adjustments here and there, I've gone through all
of the weapons, and all armor under lvl 35 and applied the changes.
 
WHAT THIS MEANS TO YOU THE PLAYER:
----------------------------------
No longer will you be able to walk around with 40,000 pounds of gear.
Things have weight. In some cases they've gotten lighter, but in most
cases not.
 
Some of your favorite dual-wield combos may no longer work. Sorry, but you'll
have to deal with it. Weight values have been established on a much more
realistic and balanced scale, and other than a couple of small tweaks here
and there, chances are they're gonna stay that way. HOWEVER - be on the
lookout for other potential combinations... Options have been added as well
as removed, so like it sez in HELP DUAL, it's on you to find em.
 
Blacksmiths will probably find themselves up to their ears in materials for
awhile, due to the formula involved in DISMANTLE. This is something I'm hoping
to rework with Pal at a later date.
 
I'll be on the lookout for any MAJOR issues that may arise, but please do
not bug me or the staff griping because you can no longer walk around with
a Golden Glaive in one hand and a Frostreaver in the other. Changes are part of
the game, and in this case were done for the purposes of consistancy, balance,
and a certain degree of "realism".
 
Enjoy ;)
 
P.S. - Any weapons you already had in your posession will NOT be affected by
this. Changes will apply to all newly loaded objs from here on.
