Subject Sizing~
Text
Ok guys - the resizing is done. All mobs, armor and weapons have now
been assigned a size value, so if you can no longer use/wear something
you could before, you'll just have to adjust because those items are
set that way on purpose. Having said that, here are a few bits of info
to consider before the complaints start rolling in:
 
1) Large creatures will find themselves unable to effectively wield
   most smaller weapons. Same thing with small creatures and large
   weapons. Don't expect to be seeing dwarves wielding greatswords,
   kender wielding huge battleaxes and Minos fumbling around with
   short blades and tiny daggers.
 
2) Whenever possible, items were sized according to the race of the
   MOB wearing it (duh.), or what race the item was MADE for. Shops
   however, will continue to custom make most armor to fit.
 
3) Most of the world population is made up of medium sized creatures;
   therefore, larger and smaller races will have a somewhat tougher time
   finding some kinds of gear. This is simply an inherent challenge of
   being a "minority", and one that you will have to rise to meet.
 
4) Minotaurs will be at a disadvantage to finding headgear (even if it IS
   large-sized) due to the problem of fitting it around their horns. This
   is intentional and based in common sense.
 
and lastly:
 
5) While they may be rare or hard to find, exceptions DO exist to just
   about every category. They may not be the ones YOU would prefer, but
   they are out there. If they aren't the "good" ones in your opinion, such is
   life. Toughen up your hide and make the best of it.
 
This game is about challenge and diversity, and we continue to work to
bring you both. Use it to your advantage instead of complaining that you
don't have the same gear as 98% of everyone else ;)
 
Enjoy!
 
- Gilean
