  Image spell, but either nobody wanted to report it until recently, by Rihivan,
  or nobody could figure out what it was that caused a crash, because to them, they
  were just moving. Turns out, when MIRRORED, and those Mirrored images were
  in the room with you, and you moved in a direction, and the room you were moving
  from happened to have an EXIT trigger on it, it would crash the MUD. I set the
  Mirror Image code up so that the MOBS would be placed in a Random order, so when
  you moved, it would actually make those MOBS move first, before you (code wise),
  but at the same time. So, it would end up bypassing the NPC check. This is fixed,
  however, there may still be some more BUG's out there pertaining to other triggers
  we have, when it comes to triggering them while with Mirror'd images of yourself.
  So, if the MUD happens to crash while you have Mirror'd images with you, re-cast
  that spell, and see if you can do it again. If it crashes again, then you found
  a BUG. Please report it, do NOT exploit it, and then try to avoid doing it again.
 
