** The final change that has been implemented in, which is actually quite
a large change, is on Land Control.  There are ** 3 ** ...  I said, THREE,
different states of control that every AREA in the GAME can and will be in. 
These STATES are as follows: Controlled by Solamnic Knights; Controlled by
the Knights of Takhisis, AND Uncontrolled by ANY military forces.  Now,
Palanthas and Neraka (which there's actually 2 area files that make up
Neraka, so include Neraka2), will ALWAYS be under specific control. 
Palanthas, under the KoS, and Neraka under the KoT.  These control factors
can NEVER change.  As well, ANY land which is Uncontrolled...  ALSO can NOT
be changed.  I do NOT want the entire MUD being under complete control by
only 2 occupying forces, so I have written an Uncontrolled Flag in order to
mark certain areas as being uncontrolled.  However, ANY area, besides the
areas listed above, that IS under control by either the KoS or KoT **CAN**
change control.  This means for example, that if say an area is under the
control of the KoT, it could potentially change sides and control could be
gained by the KoS.  However, control can always go back and forth.  This
will help give some realism to the game, spice up the flavor a little bit
and make you, the players, feel like you can control the outcome of some of
the GAME yourself.  Now, how does control over an area change???  Quite
simple, and this will not change, so please don't bother me with "ideas" on
things that could further change the control over an areas...  What is set
up now, is plenty enough.  Control can go to either side through any of the
following means: 
 
- A Solamnic Knight kills Knight of Takhisis
- A Knight of Takhisis kills a Solamnic Knight
- A Conclave Wizard kills a Knight of Takhisis
- A Blackorder member kills a Solamnic Knight
 
Now, if a Blackorder or Conclave is killed by ANY part, control over the land will
NOT change. Only the death of a Solamnic Knight or Knight of Takhisis can actually
change the control over an areas.
 
Control is determined on a point system. Of course, this point scale can NOT be
seen by any Player, nor Immortal. It is purely in the code. However, I will say
this. If a Solamnic or KoT member does the killing, control over that area (the
area in which the Solamnic or KoT who's being attacked, dies in) then the area
will change control in favor of the victor more quickly, than what it will change
if say, the successor was a Conlave or Black Order member. (2 points KoT or KoS
does the killing / 1 point of conclave/balck order does the killing). With this
one of the things that has bearing on who controls what lands, is in the case
of the APPREHEND command. Solamnics will NOW only be able to APPREHEND criminals
in Solamnic Controlled areas.
 
Now, how do you check to see who controls what area? Well, ANYONE and EVERYONE can
see who has control over an area, if any, by utilizing a new command called:
OCCUPANCY. This command will show you who has control, of course if there is no
control, it will tell you that too ;-) So far, this is the only thing that has any
REAL bearing on controlled lands, but stay tuned for future changes that will
possibly include land control, where who has control will make a difference.
 
Currently, I have YET to set the areas up with the appropriate flags, so give it
a few days before I have all the lands set with the correct control flags. As well
let it be known that Area control, can NOT be an only reason to PK someone. PK Rules
are still the same, and MASS PKing someone to change the control of an area over
quickly, will definately not be tolerated. I tested the code over and over, so
there shouldn't be any problems. If you think you found one, feel free to report
it, but just keep in mind, chances are it seems broke, only because you have made
your own assumptions as to how something should work, and it doesn't work like those
assumptions.
 
Enjoy the changes....
 
Hiddukel
