Subject New addition to the FOR Command~
Text
The level 107 Immortal command, FOR, has been modified so that you can target
players of a specific level and higher.  This argument does NOT mean that
it will only affect those of the SAME level... it will affect ALL players
(except yourself) of the same level OR higher, than the argument you entered.
Naturally, I programmed it so that you can not enter in a value below 1, nor
a value that exceeds 110.
 
I added this option to the FOR command because there were times where I wanted
to reward players with XP for roleplay, but wanted to give players at higher
levels a greater amount than those who were sitting at the bottom levels.
So now if I want to reward all players in the game who are at least level 40
or higher with 5K XP, I can... and it will only be given to those players.
If I wanted to do it in a range... and I figured I'd give players at 40+
5K, and players below that level only 2K, I'd first give those level 40+ 3K,
then I'd execute the FOR command again, but make the argument much lower and
give everyone 2K... so now the higher levels have a total of 5K, and those in
the lower level range only get 2K.
 
I didn't add in an addition argument to specify <ABOVE> or <BELOW>, but may
do so in the future.
 
- Hiddukel
