There is a new Immortal command (backcheck) that will allow Immortals to view
everyone's background.  This will be another instrumental tool Roleplay Imms
will now have to really get a feel for how well a player's roleplay truely
is.  Now, I do have plans to write code that will also allow mortals to be
able to view other people's backgrounds as well, but haven't quite figured
out all the details on how it will work.  I don't want a command that will
allow any player to check anyone's background at a whim.  I'd like it to be
something where it's a mutual agreement... that one must have introduced
themselves to the other person, before that other person can see their
background.  I just haven't come up with the best way to program it yet that
won't eat away at memory.... like if I just appended to player files with
a new section of players that one has introduced themselves to, pfile size
could get out of control and create potential for corruption.  I will keep
