I didn't want to import the changes I already have over quite yet until I
had a few more, but until I get this BUG on the development port figured
out, I would have needed to put it off longer.  I wanted to at least provide
some changes for some of you to enjoy, so here they are: 
 
* For the Undead who no longer hunger but have to drink blood to quench
their thirst; drinking blood and not having to eat still carries a penalty
when compared to drinking water to quench one's thirst, but the quench
variable has been changed from 2 to 5 per drinking action.  This should
help alleviate some of the constant burden of having to drink so much.

* Clerics gained a new level 70 skill called Relegate.  This skill will
allow a Cleric to "push" someone into a dimensional rift, removing them
from a temple and sending them to a random room somewhere within the
same vicinity (area). This serves as both a good RP tool in regards to
those who cause RP chaos in temple safe rooms, and also as an tool to
help alleviate the problem of people who run around trying to PK, and
then run off to safe room temples to avoid retribution.  This skill has
no fail chance (other than the normal failure of working due to the
percent of the skill learned not being at 100). However, Clerics MUST
be devoted to a religion and MARKED by respective God in order to use
this skill.  Likewise, Clerics can not use this skill on other fellow
Clerics.  And this skill can ONLY be used in rooms marked as a temple
(room flag is what is checked here, not room description... so some
rooms that have a light description of being a "temple", may not truely
be marked as a temple room, and therefor the skill won't work).
- Skill idea came from Divine-Light on the forums.
 
* Banish and Vortex have been fixed so that they won't transport people
to rooms marked as being no_recall, immortal only, etc..

* The GROUP command has been modified so that you can see your GROUP stats
even while sleeping.

* The pool in the Undead clan hall has been modified and now offers blood
as a liquid, versus water.

* New help file suggested by Silynt in regards to the Conclave Test has
been added as she had posted. I've already deleted the post from the forum,
so you'll have to read the help file to see what she had written.  Following
up on Conclave matters, I registered a username on the old Conclave forums
that Darkahn had created.  If any of those items would like to be added to
the MUD help files, please post your ideas on our Forums.
